Package utilities

Interface QueueADT<E>

Type Parameters:
E - The type of elements this list holds.
All Superinterfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public interface QueueADT<E>
extends java.io.Serializable
The QueueADT interface. The Queue represents a data structure designed to have elements inserted at the end of the queue, and elements removed from the beginning of the queue. A Queue is a linear ADT, in which the first element inserted is the first element to be retrieved. First In/First Out(FIFO).
Version:
March 20, 2021
Author:
Jaehan Kim, Donghyun Kim, Maria Laura Diaz Pena

    • enqueue

      void enqueue​(E toPush)
      Puts the element E to the tail of the queue. This has the same effect as: offer method. Pre-Condition: E is not null. Post-Condition: E is added to the top of the collection.
      Parameters:
      toPush - - Element to be inserted.

    • dequeue

      E dequeue()
      Retrieves and removes the head of this queue. Pre-Condition: Queue is not empty Post-Condition: Post returns the head element of this queue.
      Returns:
      E object at the bottom of this queue.

    • peek

      E peek()
      Returns the topmost element in the queue without removing it. Pre-Condition: Queue is not empty Post-Condition: Returns the top most element without removing it from the stack.
      Returns:
      E object a t the top of this stack.

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Tests if the queue is empty. Pre-Condition: - Post-Condition: Returns true if queue is empty.
      Returns:
      true if and only if this queue contains no items; false otherwise.

    • isFull

      boolean isFull()
      Tests if the queue is of static capacity. Pre-Condition: - Post-Condition: Returns true if queue is full.
      Returns:
      true only if this queue is full; false This queue is not full.

    • dequeueAll

      void dequeueAll()
      Removes all items from this queue. Pre-Condition: Stack is not empty. Post-Condition: Removes all the elements from collection.
